Preheat your oven to 200 degrees. Chop the green top and the very bottom from your @leek{1}. Slice the leek into very thin discs (1/2cm thick). Peel and chop the @onion{1/2} in half then very thinly slice half of it.

Unroll the @puff pastry sheet{1} onto a lightly greased #baking tray{}. Using a #kitchen knife{}, mark a border around the pastry, 1cm from the edge.

> Make sure you don't cut the whole way through the pastry!

Scatter the leek, onion and @walnuts{1} over the pastry. Very finely chop the leaves of the @rosemary{1} and scatter these on top. Break up the @goat's cheese{1/2} and evenly dot it across the top. Season with a good pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{} and drizzle on @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Bake for ~{15-20%mins} until the pastry has risen and is nice and golden.

> For a more golden finish, brush the 1cm pastry border with a little milk before you bake (if you have some).

Dress from head to toe in black and sneak outside to hide the evidence.

About 5 mins before your tart is ready, boil a #pot{} of water for your beans. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} to the water and cook the @green beans{1} for ~{3%mins}. Drain and keep to the side.

Serve the tart with the beans on the side.

> We like serving one large tart to cut at the table, but you can make mini ones if you like!